sed with RCov enabled generates a non-portable Ruby include option `-I`, the offending line is here:\n\nhttps://github.com/rspec/rspec-core/blob/master/lib/rspec/core/rake_task.rb#L164\n\nA simple patch is change it to read like this:\n\n```\n  cmd_parts << [\"-Ispec#{File::PATH_SEPARATOR}lib\", rcov_opts]\n```\n\nWhich might reduce readability, but works across platforms.\n\nThank you.\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/289/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/289/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}